518. Coin Change II

You are given an integer array coins representing coins of different denominations and an integer amount representing a total amount of money.

Return the number of combinations that make up that amount. If that amount of money cannot be made up by any combination of the coins, return 0.

You may assume that you have an infinite number of each kind of coin.

The answer is guaranteed to fit into a signed 32-bit integer.

Example 1:

Input: amount = 5, coins = [1,2,5]
Output: 4
Explanation: there are four ways to make up the amount:
5=5
5=2+2+1
5=2+1+1+1
5=1+1+1+1+1

Approach
Recursive
1. Base Case 
   1. If amount==0 return 1
   2. If index<0 return 0 
   3. Pefrom take,nottake 
   4. return take+nottake

Tabulation
1. Base Case
  for(int i=0;i<coins.length;i++)// amount==0
        {
            dp[i][0]=1;
        }
        for(int i=0;i<=amount;i++)// index=0
        {
            dp[0][i]=0;
        }
        dp[0][0]=1;
2. Tabulation mein yeh condition i > 0 check se already handle ho rahi hai:// becuse this condition is used in recursion when index<0
int nt = (i > 0) ? dp[i-1][t] : 0;  // ✅ i=0 pe koi previous row nahi = 0
3 return dp[coins.length - 1][amount];

//Recursive

class Solution {
    int c=0;
    public int change(int amount, int[] coins) {
        return help(coins,amount,coins.length-1);
    }
    public int  help(int []coins,int amount,int idx)
    {
        if( idx<0) return 0 ;
        if( amount==0)
        {
            return 1;
        }
        int nt=help(coins,amount,idx-1);
        int t=0;

        if( amount>=coins[idx] )
        {
            t=help(coins,amount-coins[idx],idx);
        }   
        return t+nt;
    }
}

//Tabulaion
class Solution {
    int c=0;
    public int change(int amount, int[] coins) {
        int [][]dp=new int[coins.length+1][amount+1];
        for(int i=0;i<coins.length;i++)
        {
            dp[i][0]=1;
        }
        for(int i=0;i<=amount;i++)
        {
            dp[0][i]=0;
        }
        dp[0][0]=1;
        for(int i=0;i<coins.length;i++)
        {
            for(int t=1;t<=amount;t++)
            {
                int nt=(i>0)?dp[i-1][t]:0;
                int tk=0;

                if( t>=coins[i] )
                {
                    tk=dp[i][ t-coins[i] ];
                }
                dp[i][t]=tk+nt;
            }
        }
        return dp[coins.length-1][amount];
    
        
    }
}
